From: Haoxiang Li <lihaoxiang@isrc.iscas.ac.cn>
Date: Wed, 1 Apr 2026 12:02:41 +0800
Subject: xfs: fix a resource leak in xfs_alloc_buftarg()
Git-commit: 29a7b2614357393b176ef06ba5bc3ff5afc8df69
Patch-mainline: v7.1-rc1
References: CVE-2026-46005 bsc#1267431

In the error path, call fs_put_dax() to drop the DAX
device reference.

Fixes: 6f643c57d57c ("xfs: implement ->notify_failure() for XFS")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Haoxiang Li <lihaoxiang@isrc.iscas.ac.cn>
Reviewed-by: Darrick J. Wong <djwong@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Carlos Maiolino <cem@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Anthony Iliopoulos <ailiop@suse.com>
---
 fs/xfs/xfs_buf.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/fs/xfs/xfs_buf.c
+++ b/fs/xfs/xfs_buf.c
@@ -2035,6 +2035,7 @@ error_pcpu:
 error_lru:
 	list_lru_destroy(&btp->bt_lru);
 error_free:
+	fs_put_dax(btp->bt_daxdev, mp);
 	kmem_free(btp);
 	return NULL;
 }
